sentences: Jay Leonhart (born December 6, 1940) is a double bassist, singer, and songwriter who has worked in jazz and popular music.
After studying at the Peabody Institute (1946–1950), he attended the Berklee College of Music (1959–1961) and the Advanced School of Contemporary Music in Toronto.
After studying at the Peabody Institute (1946–1950), he attended the Berklee College of Music (1959–1961) and the Advanced School of Contemporary Music in Toronto.
In the early 1960s, he worked with Mike Longo and Buddy Morrow.
In 1968, he met and married a singer named Donna Zier and settled in New York.
Between 1975 and 1995 he was named Most Valuable Bassist in the recording industry three times by the National Academy of Recording Arts and Sciences.
He has toured worldwide for more than forty years.
